when I get it back too.

85
00:11:46,830 --> 00:11:49,373
You got it, buddy.
You got it.

86
00:11:51,043 --> 00:11:54,420
Thanks a lot, Moss.
Hey, I owe ya one.

87
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:56,839
You owe me too damn many.

88
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:03,179
[Sighs]

89
00:12:05,557 --> 00:12:07,517
Oh, bombs away!

90
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:16,400
[Whimpers]

91
00:12:19,029 --> 00:12:22,114
[Growls, Barks]

92
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:29,914
[Barking Continues]
What the‒

93
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,007
[Gasps]

94
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:42,927
[Mutters]
[Dog Whimpers]

95
00:12:43,011 --> 00:12:45,429
Holy cow!

96
00:12:45,514 --> 00:12:48,432
[Barking]

97
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:56,023
[Bell Tolling]

98
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:04,073
Uh, lend me five bucks
just till tomorrow, okay?

99
00:13:04,157 --> 00:13:07,743
What for?
You know, you're not the only one with a date tonight, pal.

100
00:13:07,828 --> 00:13:11,122
I'm gonna score with Vicki tonight.
I want to invest in a little protection. Come on.

101
00:13:11,206 --> 00:13:15,334
Let's go, boys.
It's closing time. All right. Here.

102
00:13:15,419 --> 00:13:17,336
Thanks.
Make it quick.

103
00:13:20,215 --> 00:13:23,593
Uh, look, pal.
Give me a pack of Trojans and a Binaca spray.

104
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:35,897
- Scott Jeskey.
- Reverend.

105
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:38,900
Good game today!

106
00:13:38,984 --> 00:13:41,944
Uh, thanks.
Thanks, Reverend.

107
00:13:45,699 --> 00:13:50,745
How are ya?
Well, my hay fever's acting up a little bit, but I'll live.

108
00:13:50,829 --> 00:13:54,832
Yeah.
Haven't seen you at the Sunday services lately.

109
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:57,919
Oh. Yeah, well, I‒
You want the ribbed or the regular?

110
00:14:00,881 --> 00:14:03,466
Ribbed, I-I guess.

111
00:14:04,509 --> 00:14:07,219
They're not for me,
you know.

112
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:09,055
They're for my friend.
Oh?

113
00:14:10,265 --> 00:14:15,770
There's this-this-this sort of
naive girl that he's planning on‒

114
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:20,691
Well, you know. And, uh, I insisted
that he take precautions.

115
00:14:20,776 --> 00:14:23,986
Why doesn't he pay for them?

116
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:27,990
I had to drag him down here as it is.
The guy is totally irresponsible.

117
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:31,702
Hey, come on, Scott.
What's the holdup? I can't keep this girl waiting.

118
00:14:32,245 --> 00:14:36,123
The boy doesn't need condoms.
He needs a muzzle.

119
00:15:22,462 --> 00:15:25,339
[Slimy Gurgling]

120
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,383
[Growling]

121
00:15:30,929 --> 00:15:33,389
- [Gasps]
- [Whimpers]

122
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:18,225
- [Screaming]
- [Slurping]

123
00:16:21,188 --> 00:16:23,355
Kevin, don't eat with your face.

124
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:26,734
Mom, we're in a hurry.
We're gonna go bowling with Anthony.

125
00:16:26,818 --> 00:16:29,653
And then to the movies.
Ow! [Kicking]

126
00:16:29,738 --> 00:16:32,073
What movie?
Garden Tool Massacre.

127
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:34,825
It's your basic
slice-and-dice. Your basic what?

128
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:37,995
Well, this guy in a hockey mask,
he chops up a few teenagers.

129
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:41,624
But don't worry.
There's no sex or anything bad.

130
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:44,001
They won't let you kids
into a movie like that.

131
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:46,921
No problem.
My brother's an usher.

132
00:16:47,005 --> 00:16:50,174
[Scoffs]
No. Absolutely not.

133
00:16:50,258 --> 00:16:52,593
Mom, come on.
Kevin!

134
00:16:52,677 --> 00:16:57,765
I will not have you seeing
that kind of trash, and that's final. Do you understand?

135
00:16:57,849 --> 00:17:01,769
Yes, ma'am.
[Girl] Mom, have you seen my pink sweater?

136
00:17:01,853 --> 00:17:04,105
Uh, it's on the hamper,
honey.

137
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:06,732
I meant to talk to you
about that.

138
00:17:06,817 --> 00:17:08,901
Why did you do that?
What did I do?

139
00:17:08,985 --> 00:17:12,029
We, uh, had
a little accident.

140
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:18,160
What happened?
It got mixed up in the wash.

141
00:17:18,245 --> 00:17:21,872
Interesting look.
Why don't you wear my cashmere sweater?

142
00:17:21,957 --> 00:17:24,166
Are you serious?
Sure.

143
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:27,128
[Doorbell Rings]
Oh, my God, that's him.

144
00:17:31,675 --> 00:17:34,635
- What do you want?
- Hi. I'm here to see Meg.

145
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:39,974
- What for?
- Uh, just to see her.

146
00:17:40,058 --> 00:17:42,393
Is she home?
Just a minute.

147
00:17:42,477 --> 00:17:45,104
[Door Slams]
[Scoffs]

148
00:17:49,734 --> 00:17:52,403
I'm terribly sorry.
You must be Paul.

149
00:17:52,487 --> 00:17:54,613
I'm Meg's mother.
Hi. Nice to meet you, ma'am.

150
00:17:54,698 --> 00:17:57,783
Well, come on in.
Meg'll be right down.

151
00:18:00,954 --> 00:18:03,622
Uh, where do you think
you're going? Sleeping over at Eddie's.

152
00:18:03,707 --> 00:18:06,959
Oh, right.
But you're not going anywhere without your jacket.

153
00:18:07,043 --> 00:18:09,628
Oh, Mom, it's boiling out.

154
00:18:09,713 --> 00:18:12,923
Well, it's October.
It's nighttime. You're wearing your jacket.

155
00:18:13,008 --> 00:18:15,342
[Sighs, Grunts]

156
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:18,012
Stupid coat.
No, here, let me.

157
00:18:18,096 --> 00:18:21,473
Okay. Bye-bye, honey.
Enjoy yourself. Bye, Mom.

158
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:23,893
Bye, Eddie.
Oh, yeah.

159
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:28,564
Won't you sit down?

160
00:18:28,648 --> 00:18:31,066
[Phone Rings]
Oh, excuse me.

161
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:35,905
Hi, Paul.
Hi.

162
00:18:35,989 --> 00:18:39,575
Are you surviving
my family so far? Yeah. You look great.

163
00:18:39,659 --> 00:18:41,577
Thank you.
You wanna go?

164
00:18:41,661 --> 00:18:44,455
Sure. I just want you
to meet my dad really quick. It'll just take a second.

165
00:18:44,539 --> 00:18:46,457
Sure.

166
00:18:50,754 --> 00:18:53,380
Daddy, I'd like you
to meet my friend Paul.

167
00:19:00,138 --> 00:19:01,680
Ribbed.

168
00:19:06,603 --> 00:19:08,520
[Birds Chirping]

169
00:19:24,996 --> 00:19:26,956
[Twig Snapping]

170
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:47,851
[Rustling]

171
00:19:57,862 --> 00:20:00,656
[Screaming]

172
00:20:07,455 --> 00:20:09,623
[Grunting]

173
00:20:13,461 --> 00:20:15,379
Hey!

174
00:20:21,970 --> 00:20:25,347
I'm really sorry about my dad.
I've never seen him like that before.

175
00:20:25,432 --> 00:20:27,308
Th-That's okay.

176
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:29,476
It was just a misunderstanding.

177
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:31,478
[Laughing]

178
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:33,897
I've made better
first impressions though. That's for sure.

179
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:39,320
Well, no harm done,
I guess. No, wrong.

180
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:41,780
Scott Jeskey is gonna die.

181
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:49,872
- Paul, watch out!
- [Tires Screech]

182
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:56,503
Flagg! Jesus Christ!
What did you do to him?

183
00:20:56,588 --> 00:21:00,090
Hey, I'm not the one
who bounced him off my car, pal. You ran him in the road!

184
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:02,634
Stop it!
Let's get him to a doctor. Hey, watch out.

185
00:21:02,719 --> 00:21:05,637
He's got some kind
of corrosive shit on his hand.

186
00:21:07,098 --> 00:21:09,683
Come on.
Take it easy, mister.

187
00:21:09,768 --> 00:21:12,770
We're gonna get some help,
all right?

188
00:21:12,854 --> 00:21:15,189
Let's go. Come on.

189
00:21:15,273 --> 00:21:17,232
[Whimpering]

190
00:21:19,277 --> 00:21:22,988
- The sky. It fell from the sky.
- What's he sayin'?

191
00:21:23,073 --> 00:21:25,240
He's in shock.
Let's just go.

192
00:21:26,868 --> 00:21:29,328
Hey! Get in the car.

193
00:21:30,747 --> 00:21:32,331
What for?

194
00:21:32,415 --> 00:21:35,793
There's gonna be a lot of explaining to do,
and you're part of it.

195
00:21:35,877 --> 00:21:38,712
Now, are you gonna get in the car,
or am I gonna make you get in?

196
00:21:40,673 --> 00:21:42,591
What's the matter, Taylor?

197
00:21:42,675 --> 00:21:46,887
You worried about
a little insurance claim on Daddy's car, huh?

198
00:21:46,971 --> 00:21:49,181
Maybe I will come along...

199
00:21:49,265 --> 00:21:51,892
just to make sure you don't
blame this whole thing on me.

200
00:21:51,976 --> 00:21:53,769
Are you two finished?

201
00:22:07,742 --> 00:22:09,910
Whenever you're ready.

202
00:22:09,994 --> 00:22:11,954
[Engine Starts]

203
00:22:17,293 --> 00:22:19,211
Right here.

204
00:22:20,713 --> 00:22:24,216
Excuse me, Nurse?
One moment, please.

205
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:38,021
- Now, how may I help you?
- We've had a car accident. This guy needs a doctor.

206
00:22:38,106 --> 00:22:42,192
He has something on his hand too‒
some kind of acid or something.

207
00:22:44,112 --> 00:22:46,029
Does he have Blue Cross?

208
00:22:46,114 --> 00:22:48,449
I don't know.
Medical insurance of any kind?

209
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:52,077
- I don't believe this shit.
- Look, we don't even know who the guy is.

210
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:56,373
[Sighs] The doctor's with
another patient right now. [Buzzes]

211
00:22:59,085 --> 00:23:01,879
Could you put this gentleman
in room three, please?

212
00:23:04,382 --> 00:23:06,300
You'll have to
fill these out.

213
00:23:06,384 --> 00:23:08,719
Okay. Come on, up. Up.

214
00:23:11,306 --> 00:23:13,223
[Groans]

215
00:23:13,308 --> 00:23:15,267
Hey, take it easy,
old dude.

216
00:23:15,351 --> 00:23:18,979
These guys are gonna
fix you right up.

217
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:29,865
Hey, where you goin'?

218
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:34,369
These people don't give a shit
about explanations.

219
00:23:34,454 --> 00:23:37,414
If you need me,
you know where to find me.

220
00:23:49,844 --> 00:23:51,762
[Sighing]

221
00:23:59,103 --> 00:24:01,188
[Sighs]

222
00:24:01,272 --> 00:24:04,399
I bet you've had
better first dates, huh?

223
00:24:04,484 --> 00:24:06,443
I don't mind.

224
00:24:07,737 --> 00:24:09,738
Want a soda?

225
00:24:09,822 --> 00:24:13,283
Yeah, sure.
That'd be great. Something diet.

226
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:43,981
[Man]
Absolutely. At this point the prognosis is very positive.

227
00:24:44,065 --> 00:24:45,983
In cases like this,

228
00:24:46,067 --> 00:24:50,404
the question is always
the quality of physical therapy.

229
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:54,575
The follow-up to any operation
is to a great extent...

230
00:24:56,327 --> 00:24:58,245
[Slimy Gurgling]

231
00:25:08,298 --> 00:25:10,716
Doctor, come in here quickly!

232
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:14,303
I'm with a patient...
There's a man dying in here! Hurry!

233
00:25:15,972 --> 00:25:17,889
Excuse me a moment.

234
00:25:25,023 --> 00:25:27,608
Is this the hand injury?

235
00:25:39,037 --> 00:25:43,123
- What is this?
- That thing on his hand.

236
00:25:47,211 --> 00:25:48,587
Nurse!

237
00:25:58,765 --> 00:26:01,099
Sheriff's Department.
Get me the sheriff! It's an emergency.

238
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:06,813
Paul?

239
00:26:14,697 --> 00:26:17,491
Geller speaking.
Sheriff, this is Paul Taylor.

240
00:26:17,575 --> 00:26:22,913
Paul, what's wrong?
I'm at the Arborville Hospital. An old man's been killed here.

241
00:26:22,997 --> 00:26:25,123
You said "killed"?
Yes, sir.

242
00:26:25,208 --> 00:26:27,668
Okay, you sit tight. I'll be right down.
Now, who else is involved?

243
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:33,090
- I'm with Meg Penny,
and Brian Flagg was here earlier. - Flagg? Where is he now?

244
00:26:35,927 --> 00:26:38,929
[Screaming]

245
00:26:42,558 --> 00:26:45,852
Paul?
[Slimy Gurgling]

246
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:49,022
[Muffled Screaming]

247
00:26:50,858 --> 00:26:53,110
[Screaming]
Paul!

248
00:27:12,463 --> 00:27:14,965
[Dispatcher Over Radio, Indistinct]

249
00:27:21,264 --> 00:27:24,057
But I did see it, Dad.
It killed Paul.

250
00:27:24,142 --> 00:27:26,560
Shh.
Sheriff.

251
00:27:26,644 --> 00:27:28,562
How 'bout it, Herb?
Can we take her home now?

252
00:27:28,646 --> 00:27:32,733
Yeah, you may as well, Tom.
Make sure she gets a good sleep, huh?

253
00:27:35,570 --> 00:27:39,489
We're not gonna get anything
out of her tonight. She's hysterical.

254
00:27:39,574 --> 00:27:43,285
I got a call in to Paul Taylor's folks.
They haven't heard from him.

255
00:27:43,369 --> 00:27:47,372
Well, let's face it, Bill.
They're not going to.

256
00:27:49,751 --> 00:27:54,796
You get that to Sacramento tonight.
I want the autopsy pronto, not next week.

257
00:27:58,426 --> 00:28:02,012
[Car Engines Starting]

258
00:28:04,724 --> 00:28:07,559
"Jesus wept."
Herb, you okay?

259
00:28:09,854 --> 00:28:12,606
Taylor was a good kid.

260
00:28:14,442 --> 00:28:16,943
I want the son of a bitch
who did this.

261
00:28:24,368 --> 00:28:26,870
Maybe we already got him.

262
00:28:43,095 --> 00:28:46,056
♪♪ [Radio: Rock]

263
00:28:48,184 --> 00:28:50,936
Scott, cut it out.
I told you.

264
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:56,191
Come on, Vicki.
You're wearin' my ring. That makes you my girl.

265
00:28:56,275 --> 00:28:58,610
[Giggling]
Doesn't that count for something, huh?

266
00:29:01,197 --> 00:29:04,407
Hey, what are all those
lights down there?

267
00:29:04,492 --> 00:29:07,160
Isn't that the hospital?

268
00:29:07,245 --> 00:29:09,830
Yeah. It's probably
a promotional gimmick.

269
00:29:09,914 --> 00:29:12,165
They're giving away
free tonsillectomies or something.

270
00:29:12,250 --> 00:29:14,459
[Giggles]
Say, young lady,

271
00:29:14,544 --> 00:29:17,337
I think you're about ready
for another one of my famous cherry coolers.

272
00:29:17,421 --> 00:29:21,258
I think I've had enough.
Nonsense. You've never had enough.

273
00:29:34,146 --> 00:29:37,774
My very own blend
of special imported liqueurs.

274
00:29:42,488 --> 00:29:44,739
[Radio]
♪ And you feel my love ♪

275
00:29:44,824 --> 00:29:46,950
♪ All my love ♪

276
00:29:47,034 --> 00:29:49,953
♪ Tonight ♪

277
00:29:52,665 --> 00:29:54,624
[Slimy Gurgling]

278
00:30:11,809 --> 00:30:14,269
♪♪ [Continues]

279
00:30:26,782 --> 00:30:28,867
Vicki?

280
00:30:31,412 --> 00:30:34,122
Okay.

281
00:30:34,206 --> 00:30:37,500
It's like a steam bath in here.
Here's your drink, Vicki.

282
00:30:38,711 --> 00:30:40,670
Vicki?

283
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:53,141
Yep.

284
00:30:53,225 --> 00:30:55,226
Hot as a dog
out there tonight.

285
00:30:56,938 --> 00:30:58,855
Vicki?

286
00:31:04,028 --> 00:31:08,949
[Coyote Howling]
That's, uh‒

287
00:31:09,033 --> 00:31:11,117
That's a nice blouse.

288
00:31:15,456 --> 00:31:17,958
Nice material.

289
00:31:18,042 --> 00:31:22,128
Must be hot though, huh?
Yeah.

290
00:31:22,213 --> 00:31:25,715
I'll‒ I'll just
undo one of these for you.

291
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:28,009
Ah. That's better, huh?

292
00:31:29,095 --> 00:31:34,474
Oh, no? Oh, well,
I'll-I'll just...

293
00:31:34,558 --> 00:31:36,935
I'll undo another one then.

294
00:31:38,020 --> 00:31:41,481
There! Okay.

295
00:31:45,111 --> 00:31:47,570
[Sighing]
Oh.

296
00:31:55,746 --> 00:31:58,164
[Gasping]

297
00:31:58,249 --> 00:32:01,751
[Screaming]

298
00:32:01,836 --> 00:32:04,045
Vicki!

299
00:32:29,905 --> 00:32:33,825
[Father]
I knew I shouldn't have let her go out with the son of a bitch in the first place!

300
00:32:33,909 --> 00:32:38,371
[Mother]
Lower your voice. That poor boy's probably dead.

301
00:32:38,456 --> 00:32:40,874
I wanna know what happened
out there tonight.

302
00:32:40,958 --> 00:32:43,793
Whatever it was, you can bet
that Flagg kid was behind it.

303
00:32:43,878 --> 00:32:46,421
It's about time they nailed
that little psychopath.

304
00:32:46,505 --> 00:32:50,091
His ass is gonna fry
this time, believe me.

305
00:32:58,642 --> 00:33:00,560
[Sighs]

306
00:33:08,986 --> 00:33:11,696
Here. Take this.
I don't want it.

307
00:33:11,781 --> 00:33:14,407
No, come on, honey.
You have to get some sleep.

308
00:33:14,492 --> 00:33:16,493
[Sighs]

309
00:33:21,916 --> 00:33:24,167
That's my good girl.

310
00:33:26,629 --> 00:33:30,924
Now, just... let it alone.

311
00:33:31,008 --> 00:33:34,761
I'm sure that the police will have
this whole thing settled by the morning.

312
00:33:36,430 --> 00:33:37,847
Come on.

313
00:33:53,656 --> 00:33:55,573
Mom?

314
00:34:00,162 --> 00:34:02,831
You don't believe me either, do you?

315
00:34:05,167 --> 00:34:08,545
You're home now.
You're safe.

316
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:12,298
That's all that matters.

317
00:34:48,586 --> 00:34:51,588
[Slimy Gurgling]

318
00:35:13,694 --> 00:35:15,612
[Dispatcher Over Radio, Indistinct]

319
00:35:15,696 --> 00:35:20,700
Look at him.
He's too stupid to know how much trouble he's in.

320
00:35:20,784 --> 00:35:23,203
Why don't you wise up?

321
00:35:23,287 --> 00:35:25,872
I told you everything.
I'm gettin' tired of hearing myself talk.

322
00:35:25,956 --> 00:35:28,374
We're not boring you, are we‒
a bright kid like you?

323
00:35:28,459 --> 00:35:33,004
Hey, am I under arrest?
Because if I am, I want a lawyer.

324
00:35:33,088 --> 00:35:35,715
Man wants a lawyer.
Yeah, that's right.

325
00:35:35,799 --> 00:35:38,218
And if you're not bookin' me,
I'd like to leave.

326
00:35:38,302 --> 00:35:42,138
- Either way, I want you outta my face.
- Oh, yeah, hard-ass?

327
00:35:42,223 --> 00:35:45,266
Well, I'm in your face to stay.
What are you gonna do about it?

328
00:35:47,728 --> 00:35:50,230
- Go ahead, hit me!
- Bill.

329
00:35:50,314 --> 00:35:53,816
Go ahead.
[Chuckles]

330
00:35:56,153 --> 00:35:58,821
[Footsteps]

331
00:36:01,659 --> 00:36:04,410
Any luck with his mama?

332
00:36:04,495 --> 00:36:07,997
- I can't seem to find her.
- That's not unusual, is it?

333
00:36:08,082 --> 00:36:13,044
She takes little vacations
with her pal Johnnie Walker Red and anyone else who happens to be around.

334
00:36:13,128 --> 00:36:15,588
Of course, we could call his dad,
if anyone knew who he was.

335
00:36:15,673 --> 00:36:18,549
Hey, call a shrink.
I'm a broken man.

336
00:36:18,634 --> 00:36:21,094
You think this is a joke?

337
00:36:30,938 --> 00:36:33,564
Turn him loose.

338
00:36:33,649 --> 00:36:36,067
Herb, we got eyewitnesses
placing him at the scene of the crime.

339
00:36:36,151 --> 00:36:38,736
No motive, no evidence.

340
00:36:38,821 --> 00:36:41,739
He hasn't got
a drop of blood on him.

341
00:36:41,824 --> 00:36:45,368
Hell, Flagg's a punk,
but he's no killer. I think it's a mistake.

342
00:36:45,452 --> 00:36:49,914
Well, your objection is duly noted.
Now, turn him loose. We got work to do.

343
00:36:52,376 --> 00:36:54,335
Go on.

344
00:36:58,716 --> 00:37:02,051
[Handcuffs Click]
Take a hike.

345
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:15,565
Brian,
I need to talk to you.

346
00:37:22,072 --> 00:37:25,325
Brian.
What the hell are you doin' here?

347
00:37:25,409 --> 00:37:28,036
Look, I came down
to bail you out.

348
00:37:30,664 --> 00:37:34,417
What do you think they are,
Neiman-Marcus? They don't take plastic.

349
00:37:34,501 --> 00:37:37,754
Hey, I appreciate the thought.
Now, go home, okay?

350
00:37:38,964 --> 00:37:41,507
I need to talk to you.

351
00:37:41,592 --> 00:37:44,677
Hey, I'm sorry about your boyfriend.
I really am.

352
00:37:44,762 --> 00:37:49,599
But I'm tired and hungry,
and I'm not in the mood for conversation. Okay?

353
00:38:00,277 --> 00:38:02,737
George. Franny.
¿Qué pasa?

354
00:38:02,821 --> 00:38:05,198
Hey, hotshot, we're closed.

355
00:38:05,282 --> 00:38:08,659
Aw, come on, Fran.
I've been dumped on all day. Give me a break.

356
00:38:08,744 --> 00:38:12,538
Oh, what's the matter, dear?
Tough day at the office?

357
00:38:12,623 --> 00:38:14,874
[Scoffs]
Well, grill's shut down.

358
00:38:14,958 --> 00:38:17,585
- How 'bout a sandwich?
- Beautiful.

359
00:38:30,724 --> 00:38:33,267
Geez, you don't give up, do you?

360
00:38:34,978 --> 00:38:36,354
I need your help.

361
00:38:36,438 --> 00:38:39,816
For three years in school
you haven't said shit to me.

362
00:38:39,900 --> 00:38:43,444
Now all of a sudden, what...
you need my help, and we're best friends, right?

363
00:38:44,655 --> 00:38:48,366
Nobody believes me
about what happened tonight.

364
00:38:48,450 --> 00:38:52,203
- What did happen?
- You were there. You saw.

365
00:38:52,287 --> 00:38:56,332
All I saw was an old man with a funky hand.
That's all I saw.

366
00:38:58,961 --> 00:39:01,921
Thanks.
Can I get you somethin', hon?

367
00:39:02,005 --> 00:39:03,464
No, thank you.

368
00:39:10,013 --> 00:39:15,935
The thing on that man's hand
killed him, and then it killed Paul.

369
00:39:16,019 --> 00:39:19,021
And whatever it is,
it's getting bigger.

370
00:39:19,106 --> 00:39:21,816
Is that what you told the cops?

371
00:39:29,616 --> 00:39:32,034
Do you mind if I ask you
a personal question?

372
00:39:33,704 --> 00:39:37,331
I know you're
the homecoming queen type and all, but, uh,

373
00:39:37,416 --> 00:39:39,959
are you strung out
on somethin', or what?

374
00:39:40,043 --> 00:39:41,419
[Chuckles]

375
00:39:41,503 --> 00:39:44,547
[Scoffs]
You're just the same.

376
00:39:46,008 --> 00:39:48,259
What are you talkin' about?

377
00:39:48,343 --> 00:39:52,388
You act like you're different.
You put on this big show.

378
00:39:52,473 --> 00:39:57,143
But you're just like
everybody else in this town. You're full of shit, Flagg!

379
00:39:57,227 --> 00:39:59,145
Hey, wait a second.

380
00:40:01,857 --> 00:40:03,983
Hey, calm down, all right?

381
00:40:04,067 --> 00:40:06,027
I'm sorry, okay?

382
00:40:07,321 --> 00:40:09,238
Come on, sit down.

383
00:40:12,117 --> 00:40:14,035
[Sniffling]

384
00:40:17,414 --> 00:40:20,041
You okay, huh?

385
00:40:22,586 --> 00:40:24,670
You want somethin' to eat?

386
00:40:24,755 --> 00:40:27,965
Here. Go ahead.
It'll make you feel better.

387
00:40:28,050 --> 00:40:30,301
[Scoffs]
Unbelievable.

388
00:40:32,513 --> 00:40:37,808
No, it's just I've never heard
you say the word "shit" before. What was that like for you?

389
00:40:37,893 --> 00:40:39,852
[Chuckles]
[Laughs]

390
00:40:50,781 --> 00:40:52,949
We're comin' up empty here.
Do you want us to head into the foothills?

391
00:40:53,033 --> 00:40:55,826
[Sheriff Over Radio]
Negative. No, I'd rather have you patrolling the streets.

392
00:40:55,911 --> 00:40:59,121
We'll start all that at first light
when the state police come in.

393
00:40:59,206 --> 00:41:01,874
Ten-four.
You look exhausted.

394
00:41:01,959 --> 00:41:04,252
It's been a long night.
Thank you.

395
00:41:04,336 --> 00:41:07,547
It's gonna be even longer.

396
00:41:07,631 --> 00:41:10,841
That's the truth.

397
00:41:10,926 --> 00:41:12,969
One deputy and six volunteers.

398
00:41:13,053 --> 00:41:16,973
I feel like the one-legged man
in an ass-kicking contest.

399
00:41:17,057 --> 00:41:22,311
Well, you're doing all you can, Herb.
This isn't your normal Friday night trouble.

400
00:41:22,396 --> 00:41:25,022
Something wrong?
I'm, uh‒

401
00:41:25,107 --> 00:41:28,568
I'm just worried
about a friend of mine.

402
00:41:28,652 --> 00:41:31,279
I guess I'm worried
about everybody tonight.

403
00:41:36,702 --> 00:41:39,912
- Dessert?
- Oh, Fran.

404
00:41:39,997 --> 00:41:43,499
That sandwich busted me.
On the house. Last two pieces.

405
00:41:43,584 --> 00:41:45,626
Eat up, or
I chuck it in the garbage.

406
00:41:46,837 --> 00:41:48,796
[Meg]
Thanks.

407
00:42:02,728 --> 00:42:05,021
[Gurgling]

408
00:42:09,401 --> 00:42:12,570
[Sighs]
Shit.

409
00:42:23,165 --> 00:42:25,124
Here, here.
I'll get that.

410
00:42:25,208 --> 00:42:27,126
I'll get it!
[Chuckling] Here.

411
00:42:27,210 --> 00:42:29,211
Knock yourself out.
Well, thanks.

412
00:42:47,439 --> 00:42:50,399
Geez.
[Sighs]

413
00:43:13,965 --> 00:43:16,258
What is this?

414
00:43:18,387 --> 00:43:21,013
[Screaming]

415
00:43:27,062 --> 00:43:30,189
George? George!
George!

416
00:43:30,273 --> 00:43:32,274
[Screaming Continues]
Fran?

417
00:43:33,610 --> 00:43:36,320
[Screaming]

418
00:43:36,405 --> 00:43:38,948
George!
Don't touch him! Don't touch him!

419
00:43:54,756 --> 00:43:56,590
Fran, come on!

420
00:44:01,972 --> 00:44:04,765
In the freezer!

421
00:44:33,837 --> 00:44:35,671
[Screeching]

422
00:44:53,982 --> 00:44:56,317
[Panting]

423
00:44:58,195 --> 00:45:00,070
Oh! Oh!

424
00:45:02,365 --> 00:45:04,283
Hear anything?

425
00:45:07,996 --> 00:45:09,914
I'm okay.

426
00:45:14,044 --> 00:45:16,796
Hey.

427
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:20,299
I'm gonna get us outta here.
I promise.

428
00:45:28,099 --> 00:45:30,059
[Line Ringing]

429
00:45:31,102 --> 00:45:35,147
Come on.
Come on, answer!

430
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:37,399
[Gasping]

431
00:45:38,819 --> 00:45:41,570
[Recording]
Your call cannot be completed as dialed.

432
00:45:41,655 --> 00:45:44,865
Please check the number
and dial again.

433
00:45:49,079 --> 00:45:51,705
[Whimpering]

434
00:46:04,511 --> 00:46:06,929
[Woman]
Sheriff's station. Help me. Get me Herb.

435
00:46:07,013 --> 00:46:09,640
Get Herb Geller.
He went down to the diner.

436
00:46:09,724 --> 00:46:13,269
[Line Disconnects]
[Screaming]

437
00:46:14,271 --> 00:46:17,398
[Screaming]
Oh, Herb!

438
00:46:21,361 --> 00:46:23,654
[Screaming]

439
00:46:30,620 --> 00:46:31,996
You ready?

440
00:46:40,422 --> 00:46:43,340
[Hinges Creaking]

441
00:46:47,262 --> 00:46:48,721
Okay.

442
00:46:58,023 --> 00:46:59,982
Franny?

443
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:03,527
Franny!

444
00:47:16,374 --> 00:47:19,877
Great. I killed
the strawberry jam.

445
00:47:22,464 --> 00:47:25,215
Let's get outta here.
The front door's locked.

446
00:47:28,303 --> 00:47:31,347
That's okay. I got a key.

447
00:47:35,644 --> 00:47:37,561
[Bell Tolling]

448
00:47:47,822 --> 00:47:49,949
[Slimy Gurgling]

449
00:48:07,884 --> 00:48:12,096
[Gurgling Continues]
Merciful God.

450
00:48:15,892 --> 00:48:18,435
[Cat Yowling]

451
00:48:37,414 --> 00:48:40,124
Hello?

452
00:48:40,208 --> 00:48:43,377
Is anybody... hurt?

453
00:48:48,091 --> 00:48:50,009
[Cat Meowing]

454
00:48:54,931 --> 00:48:56,890
[Electricity Arcing]

455
00:49:03,106 --> 00:49:05,274
[Meowing]

456
00:49:51,071 --> 00:49:53,572
We need to see the sheriff.
I don't know where he is.

457
00:49:53,656 --> 00:49:56,575
[Phone Ringing]
Sheriff's Department. Please hold.

458
00:49:56,659 --> 00:50:01,163
- What about Briggs?
- I can't raise anybody. All I'm getting is static.

459
00:50:01,247 --> 00:50:04,041
[Ringing Continues]
Sheriff's Department. Please hold.

460
00:50:04,125 --> 00:50:08,087
The last I heard from the deputy,
he was on his way up to Elkin's Grove.

461
00:50:08,171 --> 00:50:11,673
Elkin's Grove.
That's where I found the old man.

462
00:50:11,758 --> 00:50:14,259
Come on, let's go.
[Phone Continues Ringing]

463
00:50:38,535 --> 00:50:41,537
Looks like he left
in a hurry.

464
00:50:43,581 --> 00:50:46,333
Yo, Briggs!
[Coyote Howling]

465
00:50:50,171 --> 00:50:52,881
He's gotta be
around here somewhere.

466
00:50:52,966 --> 00:50:55,634
In the woods.

467
00:50:55,718 --> 00:50:57,803
In the dark woods.

468
00:50:57,887 --> 00:51:01,181
Right.
We could wait here.

469
00:51:03,810 --> 00:51:05,727
[Sighs]

470
00:51:07,730 --> 00:51:10,482
Never thought I'd go
out of my way to find a cop.

471
00:51:13,194 --> 00:51:15,112
[Coyote Howls]

472
00:51:21,786 --> 00:51:24,496
Hello?

473
00:51:24,581 --> 00:51:27,499
I feel like fuckin'
Hansel and Gretel here.

474
00:51:27,584 --> 00:51:30,002
Should have brought
some bread crumbs.

475
00:51:32,589 --> 00:51:35,674
Wait. I think
I hear something.

476
00:51:38,428 --> 00:51:40,345
[Low Rumbling]

477
00:51:42,557 --> 00:51:45,601
What the hell is that?

478
00:52:09,459 --> 00:52:11,627
Put those weapons down.

479
00:52:15,757 --> 00:52:18,467
We're here to help you.

480
00:52:18,551 --> 00:52:20,761
Name?
Meg Penny.

481
00:52:20,845 --> 00:52:23,263
Are you a resident
of Arborville, Meg? Yes, I am.

482
00:52:23,348 --> 00:52:26,016
Have you experienced
any vomiting, nausea or diarrhea?

483
00:52:26,100 --> 00:52:30,062
Hey, back off, huh?
Hey, pal, you wanna fill us in?

484
00:52:30,146 --> 00:52:32,898
Who the hell
are you people? I'm Dr. Meddows.

485
00:52:32,982 --> 00:52:35,776
We're a government-sanctioned
biological containment team.

486
00:52:35,860 --> 00:52:37,986
"Biological containment"?

487
00:52:38,071 --> 00:52:41,365
We're microbe hunters,
young lady. Flagg?

488
00:52:42,992 --> 00:52:44,993
What are you doing here, boy?

489
00:52:46,162 --> 00:52:49,915
The men from Glad here
are showing us how to keep our leftovers fresh.

490
00:52:49,999 --> 00:52:53,752
These people are here on serious business.
They don't have time for your bullshit, understand?

491
00:52:53,836 --> 00:52:56,838
Colonel, has the deputy
been briefed in detail? Yes, sir.

492
00:52:56,923 --> 00:52:59,049
I'm just heading back to town now
to get things started.

493
00:52:59,133 --> 00:53:03,053
Splendid. Colonel Hargis
will arrange an escort.

494
00:53:03,137 --> 00:53:05,973
What is going on over there?

495
00:53:06,057 --> 00:53:09,017
That's the source of our worries‒

496
00:53:09,102 --> 00:53:11,395
a troublesome souvenir
from space. What?

497
00:53:11,479 --> 00:53:14,231
A meteorite.
Don't get too close.

498
00:53:14,315 --> 00:53:16,775
There's danger
of contamination.

499
00:53:16,859 --> 00:53:20,445
[Meg]
I don't understand. Let me tell you a story.

500
00:53:20,530 --> 00:53:24,908
The dinosaurs ruled our planet
for millions of years,

501
00:53:26,035 --> 00:53:29,037
and yet they died out
almost overnight.

502
00:53:29,122 --> 00:53:31,081
Why?

503
00:53:31,165 --> 00:53:36,295
The evidence suggests
that a meteor fell to Earth bearing an alien bacteria.

504
00:53:36,379 --> 00:53:39,298
Plague? Is that what
this whole thing is about?

505
00:53:39,382 --> 00:53:41,300
Prevention.

506
00:53:41,384 --> 00:53:44,511
And you think this meteor
brought some kind of a killer germ?

507
00:53:46,014 --> 00:53:50,309
It's something I've expected
and prepared for all my life.

508
00:53:50,393 --> 00:53:53,645
Well, your meteor
brought somethin', all right.

509
00:53:53,730 --> 00:53:58,900
But if it's a germ,
it's the biggest son of a bitch you've ever seen.

510
00:54:07,076 --> 00:54:10,454
[Small Engine Revving]
What's the matter?

511
00:54:10,538 --> 00:54:13,915
Isn't it awfully late
to be trimming the hedges?

512
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:16,668
Maybe this guy's
a Peeping Tom or something.

513
00:54:16,753 --> 00:54:19,671
So let's give him
something to peep at.

514
00:54:23,551 --> 00:54:25,719
[Engine Revving]

515
00:54:27,430 --> 00:54:31,266
Wait a minute.
Hockey season ended months ago.

516
00:54:33,603 --> 00:54:35,687
[Chuckling]
Watch this.

517
00:54:35,772 --> 00:54:38,398
He's gonna get
the camp counselor with the hedge trimmer.

518
00:54:38,483 --> 00:54:41,360
[Screaming]

519
00:54:43,654 --> 00:54:45,614
I'll bet
the girl gets away.

520
00:54:46,949 --> 00:54:52,371
Ooh, watch. She's gonna
run in the lodge and hide, but he's gonna get her anyway.

521
00:54:52,455 --> 00:54:54,456
[Screaming]
Please be quiet.

522
00:54:54,540 --> 00:54:57,667
- You shut up.
- Hey!

523
00:54:57,752 --> 00:55:01,588
You guys gotta shut up.
If you get caught in here, Mom's gonna kill me.

524
00:55:01,672 --> 00:55:05,008
Get your feet off the seat.
Anthony, come on.

525
00:55:06,969 --> 00:55:10,222
What a jerk.
What a wimp.

526
00:55:11,474 --> 00:55:14,059
Check out the body
on the blonde.

527
00:55:33,663 --> 00:55:35,997
[Muffled Gurgling]

528
00:55:49,637 --> 00:55:51,555
Wonderful.

529
00:55:56,144 --> 00:55:59,104
[Man Over Intercom] Yeah?
It's Hobbs. Listen, it's boiling up here.

530
00:55:59,188 --> 00:56:01,982
The air conditioning on?
It's on full blast.

531
00:56:02,066 --> 00:56:04,109
Yeah, well, it must be
blocked up or somethin'.

532
00:56:04,193 --> 00:56:08,405
There's nothing wrong
with the air conditioning. Come up and see for yourself.

533
00:56:23,337 --> 00:56:25,255
[Slimy Gurgling]

534
00:56:27,341 --> 00:56:29,259
[Screaming]

535
00:56:38,644 --> 00:56:40,562
Hobbs?

536
00:56:46,736 --> 00:56:48,904
Hobbs, are you in here?

537
00:56:52,867 --> 00:56:55,327
[Gasps]

538
00:56:55,411 --> 00:56:57,621
[Groaning]

539
00:57:03,419 --> 00:57:05,420
[Screaming]

540
00:57:08,049 --> 00:57:09,966
I can't begin
to thank you both.

541
00:57:10,051 --> 00:57:13,011
This information
is incredibly valuable.

542
00:57:13,095 --> 00:57:15,180
Please, get in.

543
00:57:15,264 --> 00:57:17,182
Where are we going?
Back to town.

544
00:57:17,266 --> 00:57:20,602
Arborville is under quarantine
until we've isolated that organism...

545
00:57:20,686 --> 00:57:23,855
and checked every living soul
for signs of infection.

546
00:57:23,940 --> 00:57:26,900
- In the meantime, we're your prisoners.
- Not at all. You're my patients.

547
00:57:27,777 --> 00:57:29,861
Sounds like
the same thing to me.

548
00:57:29,946 --> 00:57:33,114
- Brian‒
- Young man, please, step into the van.

549
00:57:36,452 --> 00:57:38,828
Look, thanks for
the offer, Doc,

550
00:57:38,913 --> 00:57:41,748
but my bike's right back there
and we can make it back on our own.

551
00:57:41,832 --> 00:57:45,126
Hey, by the way, I love your tailor.
I gotta get me one of those.

552
00:57:47,255 --> 00:57:50,006
- [Barking]
- Get in the van.

553
00:57:54,470 --> 00:57:56,388
Van ride sounds nice.

554
00:57:59,559 --> 00:58:01,476
[Engine Starts]

555
00:58:04,188 --> 00:58:06,147
Clear.

556
00:58:19,662 --> 00:58:22,080
It's locked.
So what?

557
00:58:22,164 --> 00:58:25,959
Brian, what is with you?
You're acting like a complete jerk.

558
00:58:26,043 --> 00:58:27,919
I have a problem
with authority figures.

559
00:58:28,004 --> 00:58:31,548
- What are you doing?
- I think we ought to get out of here.

560
00:58:31,632 --> 00:58:33,925
We oughta take my bike
and blow this town.

561
00:58:34,010 --> 00:58:36,261
It's gettin' a little thick
around here, don't you think?

562
00:58:36,345 --> 00:58:39,431
That's crazy.
These people are here to help us.

563
00:58:40,766 --> 00:58:43,602
Come on, Meg.
We don't even know who they are.

564
00:58:43,686 --> 00:58:47,439
NASA? C.I.A?
The Royal Canadian Mounties?

565
00:58:47,523 --> 00:58:50,775
All I know is I saw
a bunch of unmarked trucks.

566
00:58:50,860 --> 00:58:54,738
- I think this whole thing stinks.
- Well, we can't just run out.

567
00:58:56,407 --> 00:58:59,534
Let's just think of it
as looking out for our best interests, huh?

568
00:59:04,707 --> 00:59:07,000
You coming?

569
00:59:07,084 --> 00:59:10,378
Brian, I have to go back.
My family's there‒ people that I care about.

570
00:59:10,463 --> 00:59:14,090
I'm goin'. If you're smart,
you'll come with me.

571
00:59:15,843 --> 00:59:18,261
Then go.
Take care of yourself.

572
00:59:18,346 --> 00:59:21,181
It's the only thing
you're really good at, isn't it?

573
00:59:22,350 --> 00:59:24,559
No one else ever volunteered for the job.

574
00:59:35,196 --> 00:59:37,656
Christ, Flagg.
A cheerleader.

575
00:59:49,293 --> 00:59:51,211
[Man]
Clear out. Come on through here.

576
00:59:53,756 --> 00:59:56,132
All right, back it up.

577
01:00:01,847 --> 01:00:04,849
Come on, ma'am.
[Woman Over P.A.] There is no cause for alarm.

578
01:00:04,934 --> 01:00:08,269
I repeat:
There is no cause for alarm.

579
01:00:08,354 --> 01:00:10,689
This is
a precautionary quarantine...

580
01:00:10,773 --> 01:00:13,274
due to a potential
biological hazard.

581
01:00:13,359 --> 01:00:15,110
This is a precautionary measure.
They're just gonna ask a few questions,

582
01:00:15,194 --> 01:00:17,987
and maybe give you a shot.

583
01:00:18,072 --> 01:00:19,989
Mom! Dad!
Meg!

584
01:00:20,074 --> 01:00:25,203
Oh, Meg!
Oh, thank God you're all right.

585
01:00:25,287 --> 01:00:27,205
Honey, is Kevin with you?

586
01:00:27,289 --> 01:00:29,541
No. Isn't he staying
over at Eddie's house?

587
01:00:29,625 --> 01:00:31,626
Eddie said they were
staying at your house.

588
01:00:31,711 --> 01:00:35,046
Oh, God!
He must've snuck off to that damn movie.

589
01:00:35,131 --> 01:00:37,424
What movie?
You didn't tell me about any movie.

590
01:00:37,508 --> 01:00:41,386
Sir? Excuse me, but I think
that my little brother is over at the movie theater on Main Street.

591
01:00:41,470 --> 01:00:44,222
Miss, we're going by sectors.
We'll get there shortly. But you don't understand‒

592
01:00:44,306 --> 01:00:46,224
We'll handle it, okay?
Now get back in line.

593
01:00:46,308 --> 01:00:48,309
I don't see you handling
much of anything. You on a coffee break?

594
01:00:48,394 --> 01:00:51,146
Look, mister...
Don't "Look, mister" me. I'm a taxpayer. I pay your salary.

595
01:00:51,230 --> 01:00:53,398
What are you gonna do
about finding my son? I understand you're upset.

596
01:00:53,482 --> 01:00:56,067
But if you just get back in line,
we have the situation under control.

597
01:00:56,152 --> 01:00:59,070
Did you know that
ten years ago tonight,

598
01:00:59,155 --> 01:01:01,740
there was a horrible murder
in this house?

599
01:01:01,824 --> 01:01:05,910
No. No way.
[Man Chuckling] You'll love this.

600
01:01:05,995 --> 01:01:08,329
He hot-curls her to death.

601
01:01:08,414 --> 01:01:10,290
[Chuckling]

602
01:01:10,374 --> 01:01:12,751
Mister, we're trying to watch a‒

603
01:01:12,835 --> 01:01:15,211
[Screaming]

604
01:01:20,468 --> 01:01:24,304
[Screaming, Shouting]

605
01:01:46,660 --> 01:01:48,661
Kevin!

606
01:01:57,505 --> 01:01:59,631
[Yelling]

607
01:02:09,475 --> 01:02:11,935
- Kevin!
- Meg!

608
01:02:12,019 --> 01:02:15,063
Meg! Meg!

609
01:02:29,245 --> 01:02:31,162
[Screeching]

610
01:02:33,874 --> 01:02:36,751
[Gasping]
My zipper!

611
01:02:37,920 --> 01:02:40,213
[Pounding]

612
01:02:41,590 --> 01:02:43,675
Come on! Hurry!

613
01:02:43,759 --> 01:02:45,885
Your feet!
[Screaming]

614
01:02:50,099 --> 01:02:52,058
No! Aah!

615
01:02:55,187 --> 01:02:57,814
Hurry!

616
01:03:08,617 --> 01:03:10,577
Here!
Get it up!

617
01:03:14,123 --> 01:03:16,541
Eddie!

618
01:03:16,625 --> 01:03:18,960
[Gurgling]

619
01:03:19,044 --> 01:03:21,129
[Screeching]

620
01:03:23,424 --> 01:03:25,633
Hurry! Go!

621
01:03:40,065 --> 01:03:42,901
[Screaming]

622
01:03:42,985 --> 01:03:45,737
[Kevin]
Come on, Meg!

623
01:03:45,821 --> 01:03:48,948
Meg, come on!

624
01:04:02,671 --> 01:04:04,756
[Man]
Alpha Team, do you copy? [Man #2] Affirmative.

625
01:04:04,840 --> 01:04:07,675
Status report.
Highway 31 closed.

626
01:04:07,760 --> 01:04:11,721
Phone lines down.
We've got this town locked up tight.

627
01:04:21,982 --> 01:04:23,858
On up.

628
01:04:23,943 --> 01:04:26,361
[Chattering Continues]

629
01:04:33,285 --> 01:04:36,371
[Mechanical Whirring]

630
01:04:48,050 --> 01:04:49,968
[Meddows]
We suspected that conditions in space...

631
01:04:50,052 --> 01:04:52,971
would have a mutating effect
on bacteria, but this‒

632
01:04:53,055 --> 01:04:56,140
[Man]
This activity must be what threw the satellite out of orbit.

633
01:04:56,225 --> 01:05:00,645
[Meddows]
Correct. Our little experimental virus seems to have grown up...

634
01:05:00,729 --> 01:05:04,607
into a plasmic life-form
that hunts its prey.

635
01:05:04,692 --> 01:05:07,819
A predator.
It's fantastic.

636
01:05:07,903 --> 01:05:10,780
Sir, the organism is growing
at a geometric rate.

637
01:05:10,864 --> 01:05:14,409
By all accounts,
it's at least a thousand times its original mass.

638
01:05:14,493 --> 01:05:18,329
This'll put U.S. Defense
years ahead of the Russians.

639
01:05:18,414 --> 01:05:22,667
You don't understand.
At this rate, by next week there may be no U.S.

640
01:05:22,751 --> 01:05:23,835
[Meddows]
Nonsense.

641
01:05:23,919 --> 01:05:26,170
All we have to do
is contain it properly.

642
01:05:26,255 --> 01:05:29,841
As far as the locals are concerned,
this is simply a medical quarantine.

643
01:05:29,925 --> 01:05:32,885
Nobody gets in or out.

644
01:05:40,269 --> 01:05:42,270
Dr. Meddows.

645
01:05:42,354 --> 01:05:45,648
Just for the record,
I don't agree with any of this.

646
01:05:45,733 --> 01:05:47,650
Those people's lives
are at stake.

647
01:05:47,735 --> 01:05:50,194
Don't you think I know that?

648
01:05:50,279 --> 01:05:53,781
This isn't one of
your textbook exercises, Mr. Jennings.

649
01:05:53,866 --> 01:05:58,661
This is an experiment
in biological warfare. Or hadn't you noticed?

650
01:05:58,746 --> 01:06:01,956
That organism is potentially
the greatest breakthrough in weapons research...

651
01:06:02,041 --> 01:06:04,042
since man split the atom.

652
01:06:04,126 --> 01:06:08,546
What we do here
will affect the balance of world power.

653
01:06:08,630 --> 01:06:11,674
Of course there are
lives at stake‒ whole nations, in fact.

654
01:06:11,759 --> 01:06:15,011
And that's far more important
than a handful of people in this small town.

655
01:06:16,472 --> 01:06:19,015
And that is my cross to bear,

656
01:06:19,099 --> 01:06:21,601
Mr. Jennings.

657
01:06:21,685 --> 01:06:24,395
Now, carry out your orders.

658
01:06:24,480 --> 01:06:27,065
Yes, sir.

659
01:06:27,149 --> 01:06:29,609
Colonel! Colonel,
we've got a sighting.

660
01:06:31,653 --> 01:06:33,571
Hargis here.

661
01:06:33,655 --> 01:06:37,408
Colonel, we've got an eyewitness
who says the organism pursued some civilians into the sewers.

662
01:06:37,493 --> 01:06:40,661
It's got Kevin and Eddie
and Meg down there! You gotta do something!

663
01:06:40,746 --> 01:06:43,873
Excellent! We need a schematic
of the sewer system.

664
01:06:43,957 --> 01:06:47,168
We'll contain it down there.
I want that organism alive.

665
01:06:47,252 --> 01:06:49,378
What about the civilians?

666
01:06:55,052 --> 01:06:56,886
They're expendable.

667
01:06:59,348 --> 01:07:02,100
- [Rifle Cocks]
- Get up.

668
01:07:05,854 --> 01:07:08,064
[Gunshot]

669
01:07:09,274 --> 01:07:11,109
Stop him!

670
01:07:12,444 --> 01:07:16,030
Attention!
We have an infected civilian trying to escape!

671
01:07:16,115 --> 01:07:19,242
Stop him before he reaches
a populated area!

672
01:07:39,888 --> 01:07:41,973
[Man Over Loudspeaker]
Halt, or we will open fire!

673
01:07:42,057 --> 01:07:44,475
I repeat:
Halt, or we will open fire!

674
01:07:47,980 --> 01:07:50,523
[Gunfire]

675
01:09:24,159 --> 01:09:27,954
[Woman Over P.A.]
Handicapped persons or persons in need of special assistance...

676
01:09:28,038 --> 01:09:32,458
may report to the blue station
located on the north lawn.

677
01:09:33,961 --> 01:09:36,254
Dr. Sims and Dr. Divatni,

678
01:09:36,338 --> 01:09:38,631
please report to Med Unit One.

679
01:09:38,715 --> 01:09:41,217
Dr. Sims and Dr. Divatni,

680
01:09:41,301 --> 01:09:45,012
please report to Med Unit One.

681
01:09:46,974 --> 01:09:49,433
Are these the schematics?
Yes, sir.

682
01:09:49,518 --> 01:09:53,271
The whole town's sitting
on a system of aqueducts‒ runoff from the mountains.

683
01:09:53,355 --> 01:09:55,773
Can the organism
be contained?

684
01:09:55,857 --> 01:10:00,444
There seem to be three main junctions‒
here, here and here.

685
01:10:00,529 --> 01:10:04,782
If we close off those valves,
I think we got it.

686
01:10:09,371 --> 01:10:11,998
Is it still after us?
I don't think so.

687
01:10:12,082 --> 01:10:16,544
I'll-I'll be good, I swear.
I'll-I'll never see a movie ever again.

688
01:10:16,628 --> 01:10:19,005
It's gonna be okay.

689
01:10:19,089 --> 01:10:22,049
Let's just find a way out of here.

690
01:10:26,179 --> 01:10:28,097
This way.

691
01:10:28,181 --> 01:10:32,268
[Man Over Radio]
Baker Team, we place you 80 meters south of valve two.

692
01:10:39,818 --> 01:10:41,736
[Rat Squeaking]

693
01:10:46,825 --> 01:10:50,494
Come on.
That's our way out of here.

694
01:10:56,084 --> 01:10:59,420
Watch out for the rat.
What rat?

695
01:11:07,012 --> 01:11:09,680
Run!

696
01:11:11,266 --> 01:11:13,142
Run!

697
01:11:18,231 --> 01:11:21,025
Get up the pole! Go!
Come on! Climb! Go!

698
01:11:25,530 --> 01:11:28,366
[Screaming]

699
01:11:28,450 --> 01:11:30,534
- Eddie!
- Meg, no!

700
01:11:30,619 --> 01:11:32,495
Get out of there!

701
01:11:34,623 --> 01:11:39,210
No! Meg!

702
01:11:40,962 --> 01:11:42,922
Meg!

703
01:11:45,133 --> 01:11:47,051
[Gasping]

704
01:12:03,318 --> 01:12:05,069
[Screams]

705
01:12:12,953 --> 01:12:15,413
[Screeching, Bellowing]

706
01:12:21,837 --> 01:12:24,046
I can't get through!
You can make it, Meg!

707
01:12:24,131 --> 01:12:26,549
Come on!
Run, Kevin! Run!

708
01:12:34,099 --> 01:12:36,684
[Gunfire]

709
01:12:36,768 --> 01:12:40,062
We have orders not to shoot.
[Screaming]

710
01:12:43,692 --> 01:12:45,901
Run, Kevin!
Go to town hall!

711
01:12:45,986 --> 01:12:48,779
- No! But Meg‒
- Do it, now!

712
01:13:09,009 --> 01:13:11,510
[Screaming]

713
01:13:20,395 --> 01:13:22,646
Meg!

714
01:13:35,410 --> 01:13:37,328
Brian!

715
01:13:52,928 --> 01:13:56,013
What are you doing?

716
01:13:56,097 --> 01:13:58,390
Hang on!

717
01:14:01,937 --> 01:14:04,230
Brian!

718
01:14:12,614 --> 01:14:14,782
You all right?
Yeah.

719
01:14:23,792 --> 01:14:27,127
Forget about it, Brian.
Let's go! Forget about it!

720
01:14:34,970 --> 01:14:38,639
[Panting]
It got 'em‒ Bigelow and Wilson.

721
01:14:38,723 --> 01:14:41,642
How do we get out of here?
They were trying to scream.

722
01:14:41,726 --> 01:14:43,936
Inside it, trying to scream.

